   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter support to priority displaced households affected by the 2017 Monsoon Floods in Dinajpur and Jamalpur districts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNDP will provide shelter assistance to a total of 8,000 displaced households: 4,500 in Jamalpur and 3,500 in Dinajpur district. Each targeted household will receive Shelter Material Package composed of: 
&#x2022;	Tarpaulin/ plastic sheet/Polythene/CI Sheet 
&#x2022;	shelter construction material
&#x2022;	and required tools (wire, nails, hoe, rope, handsaw, shovel, machete, claw hammer etc).</narrative>
